# Application Structure

## Project Overview
This is a **React 19 + Vite** application for an online Quran learning platform. It uses **React Router v6** (not Next.js, despite the `app/` folder naming convention).

## Technology Stack
- **Frontend Framework**: React 19.2.0 with Vite
- **Routing**: React Router DOM v6
- **State Management**: Zustand (stores in [store/](mdc:src/store/))
- **Backend**: Firebase (Firestore, Authentication)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with RTL support (tailwindcss-rtl)
- **Internationalization**: i18next
- **Type Safety**: TypeScript

## Folder Structure

```
src/
├── app/                    # Page components (Next.js-style naming, but React Router)
│   ├── admin/              # Admin dashboard
│   ├── booking/            # Booking flow pages
│   ├── teachers/           # Teacher listing and detail pages
│   ├── teacher-profile/    # Teacher profile management
│   ├── student-profile/    # Student profile page
│   ├── profile/            # Unified profile pages
│   ├── wallet/             # Wallet management
│   ├── support/            # Support tickets
│   └── ...                 # Other feature pages
│
├── components/             # Shared UI components
│   ├── auth/               # Authentication components
│   ├── forms/               # Form components
│   ├── layout/              # Layout components (Header, Footer, etc.)
│   ├── modals/              # Modal components
│   └── sections/            # Section components
│
├── features/               # Feature-based modules (Clean Architecture)
│   └── teachers/            # Teachers feature module
│       ├── application/     # Use cases
│       ├── domain/           # Entities & interfaces
│       ├── presentation/    # Hooks & components
│       └── services/         # Business logic
│
├── contexts/               # React Context providers
│   └── AuthContext.tsx      # Authentication context
│
├── store/                  # Zustand stores
│   ├── useAppStore.ts       # App-level state (modals, toasts, etc.)
│   └── useUserStore.ts      # User profile state
│
├── services/               # Service layer (business logic)
│   ├── teacherService.ts
│   ├── studentService.ts
│   ├── bookingService.ts
│   └── ...
│
├── infrastructure/         # External services & adapters
│   └── firebase/            # Firebase repositories
│       └── repositories/    # Repository implementations
│
├── shared/                 # Shared utilities and types
│   ├── types/               # Shared TypeScript types
│   └── utils/               # Utility functions
│
├── hooks/                  # Custom React hooks
├── models/                  # Data models
├── config/                  # Configuration files
│   └── firebase.ts          # Firebase configuration
├── constants/               # Constants
│   ├── firebaseCollections.ts  # Firebase collection names
│   └── status.ts            # Status constants
└── legacy-pages/            # Legacy pages (technical debt)
```

## Key Files
- **Entry Point**: [main.tsx](mdc:src/main.tsx)
- **App Component**: [App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) - Contains routing configuration
- **Firebase Config**: [config/firebase.ts](mdc:src/config/firebase.ts)
- **Collections**: [constants/firebaseCollections.ts](mdc:src/constants/firebaseCollections.ts)

## Important Notes
1. The `app/` folder uses Next.js-style naming but is actually React Router
2. Features should follow Clean Architecture pattern (see `features/teachers/` as example)
3. Avoid direct Firebase calls in components - use repositories/services instead
4. Legacy pages exist in `legacy-pages/` - avoid adding new code there
